properties.NAME: De Lago Resort
properties.DESCRIPTION: A peaceful and idyllic setting for short or long stays. Meals and accommodation are available.

properties.NAME: Lake Bennett
properties.DESCRIPTION: A man-made freshwater Lake located near the town of Batchelor, it is the perfect spot for a swim or a paddle in a canoe or kayak. Accessible by DeLago Resort, tourists are invited to hire canoes and kayaks and enjoy the croc-free waters for a day of fun.

properties.NAME: Sundance Farm RV Park
properties.DESCRIPTION: This large flat park is located just 2km east of Batchelor NT. The park caters to self-contained RVs and includes level sites with a dump point, fresh water, a happy hour shelter, and a communal fire pit. Our friendly Park Custodians will greet you and make you feel welcome. Batchelor is the gateway to Litchfield National Park, the most visited tourist attraction in the Top End. Pets are welcome on leads. This is a working farm so care should be taken around other activities. The RV Park is accessible from Batchelor Road. If you are heading south towards Batchelor and see the large solar farm on your left, slow down as the entrance gate is coming up on your left. The gates are locked after 6.30pm each night and you will need a code to access the park or leave after hours.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Butterfly Farm
properties.DESCRIPTION: Batchelor Butterfly Farm Accommodation has a variety of cabin accommodation options that will cater to individuals, couples and families. Groups are catered for in a 3-bedroom self-contained Homestay with beds for up to 12 people. The Restaurant is open 7 days-a-week, serving breakfast, lunch and dinner, delicious home-cooked Asian and Western-style meals using fresh ingredients from our garden where possible. Relax in the swimming pool, unwind in the shade or enjoy the Pet Garden and Butterfly House.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Holiday Park
properties.DESCRIPTION: Batchelor Holiday Park provides a range of accommodations including Powered Sites, Bush Camping Powered Sites, Grassed Shady Tent Sites, Ensuite Sites, Large Sites For Big Rigs, Ensuite Family Cabins and Luxury 2-Bedroom Villas suitable for families of 4 people or 6 people. As the sun goes down, raise a glass and enjoy the wild bird feeding in the Park, and then it’s just a short stroll for a delicious dinner in town if you don’t feel like cooking!

properties.NAME: Litchfield Outback Resort
properties.DESCRIPTION: Litchfield Outback Resort is perfectly located for exploring Litchfield National Park and its surrounds. Clean, modern rooms overlooking the sparkling cool pool will keep you comfortable for your stay. Enjoy a meal or barista-made coffee at the Lil’ Ripper Café, Bar and Bistro or take a day trip to one of the many local attractions.

properties.NAME: Pandanus on Litchfield
properties.DESCRIPTION: Stay at Pandanus on Litchfield for quality accommodation and an extensive range of resort facilities in Litchfield. Pandanus on Litchfield offers well-equipped cabins and camping sites that are just a stone’s throw away from Litchfield National Park.

properties.NAME: Banyan Tree Resort
properties.DESCRIPTION: Banyan Tree Resort is set in the fairy-lit branches of a 250-year-old Banyan Tree. Offering a wide range of accommodation options from unpowered sites to cabins, units and chalets - everyone is sure to find an option that suits them. Unwind in the evening at the bar and restaurant to soak up the atmosphere of this unique accommodation.

properties.NAME: Litchfield Tourist Park
properties.DESCRIPTION: Litchfield Tourist Park offers a true top end experience and a perfect base for your Litchfield National Park adventures. Located on the banks of the Finnis River, you can try your hand at fishing for Barra or Black Bream or just relax by the pool if you don’t feel like watching for crocs. Camping right through to homestead accommodation is available.

properties.NAME: Zebra Stone
properties.DESCRIPTION: Low-cost bush camping right on the doorstep of Litchfield National Park. Home to the stunning Zebra stone Gallery - enjoy the friendly, relaxed atmosphere and local hospitality.

properties.NAME: Batchelor General Store and Post Office
properties.DESCRIPTION: Batchelor Store stocks a range of general grocery and household items and some hot food. Fuel is also available from the store. Post office services are available from 9am-5pm, Monday to Friday.

properties.NAME: Public Toilets and Dump Point
properties.DESCRIPTION: A dump point is available for use as well as public toilet facilities.

properties.NAME: Puma Service Station
properties.DESCRIPTION: Multiple ULP and Diesel bowsers Puma service station also has ice, gas bottle exchange and grocery items.

properties.NAME: BP Service Station
properties.DESCRIPTION: Part of Litchfield Outback Resort, BP Batchelor offers a range of petrol and diesel fuels. Services include ATM, Barista Coffee, High flow Diesel - all major payment cards are accepted.

properties.NAME: Visitor Centre
properties.DESCRIPTION: Find all the up-to-date information on the local area.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Pool
properties.DESCRIPTION: A public swimming pool that offers a quick spot to refresh for all ages

properties.NAME: Batchelor Oval
properties.DESCRIPTION: Central to all the township’s amenities, Batchelor Oval plays host to many community events throughout the year. There is play equipment, a skate park and picnic areas surrounding the oval making it the perfect place to enjoy a break.

properties.NAME: Cookes Tours
properties.DESCRIPTION: Locally owned and operated Cookes Tours can personalise your local experience to encompass whatever you can dream up. With over 30 years of local knowledge, they can tailor a package that ensures you see the very best of Batchelor and its surrounds.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Immerse yourself in the history of this little township and its surrounding areas. With a rich mining, WW2 and farming history, you will be amazed how the district has come of age.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Butterfly Farm, Pet Gardens and Restaurant
properties.DESCRIPTION: At Batchelor Butterfly Farm, visitors are able to stroll amongst amazing Australian butterflies in an indoor subtropical rainforest setting. Share the world of butterflies as they fly, court, mate, sip nectar or rest in the light showing off their fascinating colours and patterns. The Batchelor Butterfly Farm will leave you with a renewed appreciation of a small animal that can be taken very much for granted. A visit to the Animal farm will allow you and the children to see and touch a variety of domestic animals, including goats, ducks and rabbit. Keep your eyes open for some animals that are native to the Northern Territory. There is also a Restaurant on site offering breakfast, lunch and dinner in a beautiful, relaxed setting 7 days-a-week.

properties.NAME: Karlstein Castle
properties.DESCRIPTION: A Replica castle handcrafted in Batchelor. Read the history of this intriguing piece surrounded by tamarind trees in one of Batchelor’s leafy parks.

properties.NAME: Lil’ Ripper Cafe, Bar and Bistro
properties.DESCRIPTION: Part of the Litchfield Outback Resort and toted as the best pub in the scrub. Enjoy a chef-prepared experience while sipping on a beautifully prepared cocktail by our passionate, friendly staff and soak in the cracking atmosphere! Open for breakfast from 9am. Bar opens at 10 am for drinks (serving our own Litchfield Lil’ Ripper Lager), have a flutter on the pokies or a game of pool - dinner service starts from 5.30 pm in the evenings. Barista coffees and scrumptious cakes are served throughout the day.

properties.NAME: Rum Jungle Lake
properties.DESCRIPTION: The site of an old mine Rum Jungle Lake has been resorted to make a beautiful lake to be enjoyed by all. Whilst swimming is not recommended due to some resident Fresh Water Crocs, Rum Jungle Lake is the ideal spot for a picnic or kayak. Throw a line in to see if you can catch one of the Barra that has been released in this picturesque spot.

properties.NAME: NT Adventure Park Quad Bike Tours
properties.DESCRIPTION: Enjoy a ride on a quad bike through Rum Jungle in Batchelor on dirt tracks with your tour guide. The tour will take you to lookouts, where you have a spectacular view of Rum Jungle.  Here you can experience the isolation previously only familiar to early Northern Territory explorers.  Guides will introduce you to native plants and vegetation along with the rich cultural history of the Batchelor and Litchfield regions.  See kangaroos, frilled neck lizards, reptiles, and a mountain of wildlife in their natural environment.

properties.NAME: Zebra Stone Museum, Gallery and Gift Shop
properties.DESCRIPTION: This is your opportunity to marvel at Zebra rocks. Have all your questions answered on the gallery tour and see how these stones polish into beautiful natural works of art.

properties.NAME: Nina’s Ark
properties.DESCRIPTION: Home to a variety of native animals, Nina’s Ark Wildlife Sanctuary is the only one of its kind in Australia. It’s unique because the wildlife that is released here returns all year on a daily basis. We describe this as living with wildlife. Twice a day an event is held that’s seen nowhere else.  Known as “Calling of the Roos”, this event sees hundreds of Kangaroos come to Nina’s call.  You will also meet many other varieties of Australian Wildlife that are currently in our care. Tours and experiences are by appointment only.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Sports Courts
properties.DESCRIPTION: Basketball and tennis courts in the centre of town, tennis net & racquets can be hired from the general store.

properties.NAME: Batchelor Community Health Centre
properties.DESCRIPTION: General practice service

properties.NAME: Batchelor Airfield
properties.DESCRIPTION: Constructed originally by US Army Engineers during WW2, the Airfield underwent upgrading numerous times to become an optional airport for Darwin should the need arise.

properties.NAME: Magnetic Termite Mounds
properties.DESCRIPTION: An amazing spectacle and must do stop on your way into Litchfield National Park. Take the opportunity to learn about the mounds and the clever creatures that inhabit them with access to an information shelter and an accessible boardwalk.

properties.NAME: Buley Rockhole
properties.DESCRIPTION: The ideal place to cool off in the Northern Territory heat - Buley Rockhole is a series of flowing streams that have carved out plunge pools in the surrounding rocks. It is a perfect place for the whole family to enjoy, with a series of shallow to deep rockpools. For those who want more than just to cool off, there is a 3.2km easy grade walk following the waterway to Florence falls. Toilet facilities are available. All vehicle access and limited car parking. There are no accessibility ramps or easy access to the water and you will need to walk over natural rock beds to access the rock pools. Picnic areas are open most of the year. Check the website for the latest park opening details.

properties.NAME: Florence Falls
properties.DESCRIPTION: It is possible to view these stunning falls from multiple vantage points. A short accessible walk from the carpark gives you access to the viewing platform to take in the majesty of these falls which are particularly spectacular in the wet season. Following this track will take you all the way down the gorge floor and give you access to the pool at the bottom of the falls for swimming. Enjoy the rush of swimming directly below one of the Northern Territories' most beautiful waterfalls. There is also the stunning Shady creek track which is an easy 1km walk from the falls back to the carpark taking in the transition from rainforest to woodland. Toilet Facilities are available. All vehicle access and car parking. There are no accessibility ramps or easy access to the water and you will need to walk over natural rock beds or stairs to access the pools. Picnic areas are available. Check the website for the latest park opening details.

properties.NAME: Tabletop Track
properties.DESCRIPTION: A 39 km circuit designed specifically for experienced self-sufficient bushwalkers, gives the adventurous the opportunity to experience the whole spectrum on offer in the park. Take an extended opportunity to camp along the way and absorb the beauty of the area. The Track is only accessible via walking. There are some facilities along the way. The Track is closed from October to June. Book and check the latest park opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: The Lost City
properties.DESCRIPTION: Approximately 10 km off the main Litchfield Park Road is the impressive sandstone pillars reminiscent of ruins from a long-lost civilisation. Forged across millions of years, these are definitely a sight to behold. Only accessible by 4WD, visitors are recommended to have high clearance vehicles and experience. The attraction is closed from November to May as the track is impassable. Check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Blythe Homestead
properties.DESCRIPTION: Accessible by the Reynolds 4WD track, take an insightful look into a homestead built in 1929. It provides a glimpse of the lifestyle of those who occupied remote Northern Territory in the pioneer days and the adversity they came up against. The attraction is closed from November to May. Check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Tjayner Falls / Sandy Creek
properties.DESCRIPTION: Accessible by Reynolds 4WD Track, Tjaynera Falls is a 1.4km walk into a secluded plunge pool. It is a perfect spot to take a break and relax. The campground comes with toilet and shower facilities and is closed from November to May. Book camping and check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Surprise Creek Falls
properties.DESCRIPTION: Also located on the Reynolds 4WD track, Surprise Creek Falls is a stunning secluded spot that offers a short walk through a monsoonal forest to sparkling rock pools and a small waterfall. The campground comes with toilet facilities and is closed from November to May. Book camping and check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Tolmer Falls
properties.DESCRIPTION: A stunning large waterfall accessible by a short 400m sealed path from the carpark to a viewing platform to soak in the Falls majesty. Tolmer Falls is the perfect wet season activity as they are even more spectacular at this time of year. Swimming and camping are not allowed. Check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Greenant Creek / Tjaetaba Falls
properties.DESCRIPTION: A picturesque 1.5 hour shady walk to Tjaetaba Falls Lookout that overlooks a sacred Aboriginal Site and the creek below. This is a moderately graded walk as there are steep inclines but as you arrive at the Falls, there is a plunge pool at the top of the falls where you can cool off and take in the native Flora and Fauna. The custodians of this land request that visitors only swim above the falls in the rockpools. There are picnic tables and toilets close to the carpark. Check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Wangi Falls
properties.DESCRIPTION: One of the most accessible swimming and picnic areas in Litchfield National Park, spend the whole day here and relax in the lawned picnic area or enjoy a refreshment at the kiosk. There are multiple walking tracks to enjoy or take a dip in the pool at the bottom of the falls (regularly closed for swimming in the wet season). Book camping and check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Cascades
properties.DESCRIPTION: Cascades is a selection of 6 plunge pools with a beautiful walk of 1km to 1.5km between each set of falls. For those who are after a walk through the incredible Australian outback, with a dip in a natural spring along the way, this Litchfield National Park gem is the one for you. There are picnic tables and toilets close to the carpark. Check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Walker Creek
properties.DESCRIPTION: A unique spot with beautiful walks and multiple swimming holes. Spend the day or stay longer to explore the swimming holes. The creek is accessible by 2WD and the camp site comes with toilet facilities. Book camping and check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.AREA: Off Litchfield Park Rd via Batchelor
properties.NAME: Bamboo Creek Tin Mine
properties.DESCRIPTION: An insight into tin mining in the early 1900s, Bamboo Creek Tin Mine has many original structures and equipment. Visiting the mine is a great way to explore and learn the history of early mining in the Northern Territory. Check the latest opening details on the website.

properties.NAME: Adelaide River War Cemetery
properties.DESCRIPTION: War Graves where service people laid to rest from the Bombing of Darwin on 19th February 1942. It also houses a Civilian section where civilians that died in the conflict are laid as well.

properties.NAME: Coomalie Bush Cemetery
properties.DESCRIPTION: A peaceful and idyllic setting for Coomalie residents.

properties.NAME: Adelaide River Railway Museum – Northern Australia Railway
properties.DESCRIPTION: Infrastructure and equipment from the original Northern Australia Railway, with static displays from WW2.

properties.NAME: Robin Falls
properties.DESCRIPTION: Situated on private land, although accessible to the public. Crocodiles can be present, swim at your own risk.

properties.NAME: Mount Bundy Station
properties.DESCRIPTION: Accommodation and meals are available. Venue hire for weddings and celebrations.

properties.NAME: Adelaide River Inn and Resort
properties.DESCRIPTION: Accommodation, a caravan park, meals, and fuel are available.

properties.NAME: WWII 4WD Tour at Pell Airstrip
properties.DESCRIPTION: Historical tour of the 4RSU (No 4 Recovery and Service Unit) site for World War II. Contact the provider for additional information.

properties.NAME: Rum Jungle Bungalows
properties.DESCRIPTION: Rum Jungle Bungalows is in the township of Batchelor, which is 18 km from the entrance to Litchfield National Park. Corporate accommodation at Batchelor Rum Jungle Bungalows is now only offering multi-night bookings to businesses, organisations and contractors. The Bungalow is an ideal base for short-term stays while working in Batchelor and surrounding regions.

properties.NAME: Adelaide River Post Office
properties.DESCRIPTION: We are a post office,ATM, newsagency, general store, liquor, hot pies, cafe and the best coffee in town

properties.NAME: Adelaide River Health Centre
properties.DESCRIPTION: Services are ONLY available to local residents.  GP hours vary, please contact us to confirm when available.  Telehealth available to existing patients who have had a face to face appointment in the last 12 months.You'll need to book an appointment before you come.Bulk billing only - No fee for this service with a Medicare card presented. You can speak to the healthcare professional by phone or video call. Wheelchair accessible, Free parking and Toilet. After-Hours Arrangements: Please call Adelaide River Community Health Centre on 08 8976 7027; Weekdays: 4PM to 8AM, Weekends: 24 hours, Public Holidays: 24 hours.
